Ahhh! It’s almost dinner! What are you having? It comes around so quickly every single day, and it’s summer! You don’t have a lot of time on your hands!

Don’t worry. We have the perfect simple and quick dinner recipe for you today, our Buffalo Chicken Sandwiches are the perfect quick and simple dinner recipe, we know you’ll love! 

You can make them in the Instant Pot or Slow cooker, or make and extra at the same time, and save it as a freezer meal for later! 

Find the full recipe on our website, SixSistersStuff.com

Beef Tips and Gravy (one of our favorite freezer meals that you can use in your slow cooker or Instant Pot!)

It is a heat wave! And we do not want to turn on our ovens or grills, so we are surviving on our Instant Pots and Slow Cookers this summer!

These Beef Tips and Gravy are so yummy, full of flavor, and literally take only a few minutes to throw together. Also, we firmly believe this recipe is the secret to a happy marriage! 💕 It’s that good. 

Head to our website to get the full recipe, and save this video for reference!

Orange Creamsicles are a staple in any self-respecting food lovers summer, right? Please tell us we're not the only ones trying to cram our freezer so we can fit just one more box of those amazing orange popsicles in there?! If your freezer is at capacity, don't worry-this recipe serves as an easy creamsicle fix! Our Orange Creamsicle Fruit Dip Recipe is a 5 minute deal-and goes well with any fruit your heart could desire. So whip this up, and kick back with some fruit-all is well with the world! Tag an orange creamsicle lover and help us spread the good news! 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “Orange Creamsicle Fruit Dip Recipe".

We aren't always ones to spend very long in the kitchen (we are all for the quick, delicious meal), but if we do, it's usually to make these Homemade Cinnamon Rolls. Guys. These are worth your time, we promise. We love to enjoy these especially when the weather cools off. With fall right around the corner, make sure to have this recipe at your finger tips the second it drops below 70 degrees! Comment below if you prefer to eat your cinnamon rolls with a fork (think ooey-gooey cinnamon rolls), or if you're of the "pick it up, and light on the frosting" school of thought. No pressure, but there is a correct answer. 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “The BEST Homemade Cinnamon Rolls".

We love greek yogurt in recipes! It's filling, full of protein (and those probiotics that we're always hearing that we should eat more of), and gives so many recipes a rich, creamy taste that's just to die for! In this recipe, however, greek yogurt isn't taking a back seat! This Greek Yogurt Fruit Salad is tangy and full of that greek yogurt tangy goodness! Get your fruit, and your protein too and try this salad as a fresh side (or as a healthy dessert!) to any main dish! 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “Greek Yogurt  Fruit Salad".

Eating your veggies should not be a chore. If you're choking down bland veggies-you're doing it wrong! Allow us to introduce you to our Instant Pot Honey Glazed Carrots Recipe-a snap to whip up and a dreamy side for a Sunday roast or any dinner that needs a pop of color (and some vitamins). Don't be too surprised to see your kids serving themselves seconds of this veggie dish-the key is to act casual; any sudden movements and they might realize that they're having seconds of cooked veggies!

With all of the grilled chicken we've been stuffing ourselves with all summer, we're still not sick of chicken! This chicken recipe is fancified just a little, with an amazing cream cheese filling and wrapped in bacon to top the whole thing off! Don't be intimidated, this preps in only 10 minutes, you'll be throwing this into the oven and letting the rest of the magic happen before you know it! We love to serve this with a big dollop of mashed potatoes or some steamed green beans-but the sky is the limit, what DOESN'T chicken go well with? 

Check out the clickable link in our bio or head to our website and search, “Bacon Wrapped Cream Cheese Stuffed Chicken".

Do you believe in magic? Nothing says "magic" like three kinds of chocolate chips in one neat cookie bar, and that's exactly what this recipe has! Our Seven Layer Bar Cookies are the realest of the real deals, and if you know what's good for you (or at least for your soul), we suggest that you take us up on this recipe as soon as possible, and make an extra batch for the neighbors while you're at it! There's nothing that this perfect blend of chocolate, coconut, nuts and *magic* can't fix! Tag someone who can hande this level of dessert, and happy baking!

Brownies kind of make the world go round, in our opinion. Need a fast chocolate fix? Brownies. Your plans got canceled? Brownies to the rescue. Your show got taken off Netflix? With lucious coconut topping on top of that fudgy chocolate brownie that we all love, this recipe will knock your socks off!

We LOVE egg rolls, but they can get messy and time consuming. That being said, we think we should live in a world where we can have egg rolls any time we want without the mess, and turns out we were right! This lightened-up recipe that we like call, "Egg Roll in a Bowl" is full of all of the delicious ingredients of an egg roll, and you won't even miss the "roll" part! Treat yourself to a big bowl of this goodness, and don't be surprised if you don't get the whole bowl to yourself-this is a family favorite for a reason!
